* Go and concurrency

Concurrency is enabled via two powerful concepts:

- goroutines
- channels

* Goroutines

In order to create a goroutine you have to do the following:

    go function

Example:

.play goroutines.go  /^func main/,/^}/

* Channels

In order to create a channel you have to do the following:

    result := make(chan float64)

Example:

.play channels.go /^func powersOf/,/^}/

* Channels advanced

.play advchannels.go  /^	var timeout/,/	os.Exit/

* Dir size example

See everything in action

.play du.go /^func walkDir/,/^}/

